com.opengamma.strata.calc.marketdata.mapping

Class MissingMapping

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.opengamma.strata.calc.marketdata.mapping.MissingMapping
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    MarketDataMapping<Void,MarketDataKey<Void>>

    public final class MissingMapping
extends Object
implements MarketDataMapping<Void,MarketDataKey<Void>>
    Market data mapping implementation used when there is no mapping for a key.

    It returns an ID indicating there was no mapping available for the key. This ID is handled by MissingMappingMarketDataFunction which creates a failure result for the data with an error message explaining the problem.

    This approach always allows configuration to be built for a set of calculations - if the market data configuration is incomplete, IDs will still be generated for all the requirements. When those IDs are processed by the market data factory, they will appear as failures in the built market data with an error message explaining the problem.

      • getIdForKey

        public MissingMappingId getIdForKey(MarketDataKey<Void> key)
        Description copied from interface: MarketDataMapping
        Returns a market data ID which uniquely identifies the piece of market data referred to by the key.

        The key might identify an item of data of which there are many instances in the system, for example the USD discounting curve. The ID identifies a globally unique instance, for example the USD discounting curve from a named curve group.

        Specified by:
        getIdForKey in interface MarketDataMapping<Void,MarketDataKey<Void>>
        Parameters:
        key - a key identifying an item of market data
        Returns:
        an ID uniquely identifying an item of market data
